                <lg type="poemPage" n="6" xml:id="poemPage06">
                    <head>
                    3
                    </head>
                    <lg type="stanza" n="21" xml:id="stanza21">
                        <l n="90"><subst xml:id="sub-15"><del xml:id="del-51" hand="VEliot">"You want to keep him at home, I suppose".</del><add xml:id="add-38" hand="VEliot"><ref xml:id="ref-1" target="note-35" hand="VEliot">*</ref></add></subst></l>
                        <l>HURRY UP PLEASE IT'S TIME.</l>
                        <l>Well thtat Sunday Albert was home, they had a hot gammon,</l>
                        <l>And they asked me in to dinner, to get the beauty of it hot-</l>
                        <l>HURRY UP PLEASE IT'S TIME.</l>
                        <l n="95">HURRY UP PLEASE IT'S TIME.</l>
                        <l>Goo<del xml:id="del-52a" hand="VEliot">d</del> night, Bill.   Goo<del xml:id="del-52b" hand="VEliot">d</del> night, Lou.   Goo<del xml:id="del-52c" hand="VEliot">d</del> night, George. Goo<del xml:id="del-52d" hand="VEliot">d</del> night.</l>
                        <l>Ta ta.   <del xml:id="del-53" hand="VEliot">Good night.   Good night.</del></l>
                        <l>Good night, ladies, good night, sweet ladies, good night, good night.</l>
                    </lg>
